  (text "VDDCORE 0.8V Buck\nVout = 0.8*(1+R1/R2) = 0.8*(1+100k/549k) ≈ 0.946V\nNote: Use R2=549k for 0.8V target per TPS62150 datasheet Eq.2\nActual: check against Vref=0.6V: Vout=0.6*(1+R_top/R_bot)\n  R_top=200k R_bot=68k → Vout=0.6*(1+200/68)=2.365V  (wrong)\n  R_top=16.9k R_bot=100k → Vout=0.6*(1+16.9/100)=0.70V\n  Final BOM values subject to revision after PDN analysis"
